Name: Zhenting Li
Directed Research Week2
Project Name: GetFirstNRows-ClientVersion
Summer 2020
----------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION

This is a program to build a email register and login application. Information of users
will be stored in a PostgreSQL database (in my code, it is NodeLogin). Users' passwords
will be hashed and then stored in the database.

----------------------------------------------
ACKNOWLEDGE ANY OUTSIDE SOURCES

Followed the tutorials of Conor Bailey on YouTube:
- Implementing User Authentication With Node JS and PostgreSQL:
  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vxu1RrR0vbw
  https://github.com/conorbailey90/node-js-passport-login-postgresql
----------------------------------------------
ENVIRONMENT SET UP AND FILE RUNNING:

- Please make sure that you've successfully installed npm by checking its version:
$ node -v
  Or you can update npm by:
$ npm install npm@latest -g

- Please go to the project directory, and use npm to install the following package:
$ npm install pg
$ npm install express
$ npm install -D nodemon
$ npm install ejs
$ npm install dotenv
$ npm install bcrypt
$ npm install passport passportlocal
$ npm install express-session express-flash

- Please change the database configuration .env to fit your database
DB_USER=postgres
DB_PASSWORD=password
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=5432
DB_DATABASE=NodeLogin

- Run server.js by:
$ npm run start
or:
$ npm run dev

- Go to http://localhost:4000/ in your browser